<subSubSection lastPageId="39" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,955,2026]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,326,1303,1329]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body yellowish to reddish brown, moderately shining. Length of pronotum + elytra = 3.9–5.7 mm (males), 3.8–6.0 mm (females). Head finely punctate, with a median longitudinal depression between eyes and extending onto clypeus. Pronotum narrow, widest at basal one-third, sides rounded, basal angles obtuse; with a pair of small basal impressions joined by an irregular row of punctures, marked by a transverse line of dark pigmentation; ratio length:width = 1:1.4; finely punctate, with no microsculpture. Elytra wider than pronotum, elongate, ratio length:width = 1:0.7; with 9 closely punctate, weakly impressed striae; striae 6 and 7 do not reach apex; intervals with 2–3 rows of fine punctures, uneven intervals with scattered larger punctures and transversely striolate. Antennal club (
<figureCitation box="[776,878,1574,1600]" captionStart="FIGURES 101–106" captionStartId="38.[151,270,1076,1100]" captionTargetBox="[260,1333,202,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-87@38.[254,1333,197,1051]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 101–106. Macrohydnobius matthewsii. 101. Right antenna, dorsal view. 102. Mandibles, dorsal view. 103. Male right protibia. 104. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 105. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 106. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 106), 0.5 mm (Figs. 104, 105), 0.75 mm (Figs. 101, 102), 1.0 mm (Fig. 103)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310957/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
) moderately slender, ratio club width:length = 1:3.1; width ratio of antennomeres 7:8:9 = 1.3:1:1.6. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[938,1041,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 101–106" captionStartId="38.[151,270,1076,1100]" captionTargetBox="[260,1333,202,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-87@38.[254,1333,197,1051]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 101–106. Macrohydnobius matthewsii. 101. Right antenna, dorsal view. 102. Mandibles, dorsal view. 103. Male right protibia. 104. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 105. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 106. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 106), 0.5 mm (Figs. 104, 105), 0.75 mm (Figs. 101, 102), 1.0 mm (Fig. 103)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310957/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 102</figureCitation>
) elongate, broad at base, narrow apically; lacking teeth on outer margins; left mandible with acute tooth on apical one-half of inner margin; right mandible irregularly dentate at middle of inner margin. Metatrochanter lacking a tooth before apex. All femora unarmed in both sexes. Male protibia (
<figureCitation box="[710,812,1729,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 101–106" captionStartId="38.[151,270,1076,1100]" captionTargetBox="[260,1333,202,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-87@38.[254,1333,197,1051]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 101–106. Macrohydnobius matthewsii. 101. Right antenna, dorsal view. 102. Mandibles, dorsal view. 103. Male right protibia. 104. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 105. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 106. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 106), 0.5 mm (Figs. 104, 105), 0.75 mm (Figs. 101, 102), 1.0 mm (Fig. 103)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310957/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
) broad at apex, spinose on outer margin, with large sinuate spur at apex; female protibia similar in shape but apical spur unmodified; mesotibia and metatibia of both sexes narrow, slightly widened apically, spinose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[790,860,1806,1832]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Male.</emphasis>
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1101,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURES 101–106" captionStartId="38.[151,270,1076,1100]" captionTargetBox="[260,1333,202,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-87@38.[254,1333,197,1051]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 101–106. Macrohydnobius matthewsii. 101. Right antenna, dorsal view. 102. Mandibles, dorsal view. 103. Male right protibia. 104. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 105. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 106. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 106), 0.5 mm (Figs. 104, 105), 0.75 mm (Figs. 101, 102), 1.0 mm (Fig. 103)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310957/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
) with median lobe elongate, narrower in apical two-fifths, triangular at apex. Parameres narrow and short, inserted at apical two-fifths of median lobe and not reaching apex; short setae apically. Internal sac with scale-like setae with tapered apices, visible as a pair of elongate rows when inverted. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[764,866,1922,1948]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Female.</emphasis>
Coxites (
<figureCitation box="[988,1094,1923,1949]" captionStart="FIGURES 101–106" captionStartId="38.[151,270,1076,1100]" captionTargetBox="[260,1333,202,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-87@38.[254,1333,197,1051]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 101–106. Macrohydnobius matthewsii. 101. Right antenna, dorsal view. 102. Mandibles, dorsal view. 103. Male right protibia. 104. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 105. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 106. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 106), 0.5 mm (Figs. 104, 105), 0.75 mm (Figs. 101, 102), 1.0 mm (Fig. 103)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310957/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
) elongate, cylindrical, with subapical setae; styli moderately elongate, inserted at apices of coxites. Sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1220,1961,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 101–106" captionStartId="38.[151,270,1076,1100]" captionTargetBox="[260,1333,202,1048]" captionTargetId="figure-87@38.[254,1333,197,1051]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 101–106. Macrohydnobius matthewsii. 101. Right antenna, dorsal view. 102. Mandibles, dorsal view. 103. Male right protibia. 104. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 105. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 106. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 106), 0.5 mm (Figs. 104, 105), 0.75 mm (Figs. 101, 102), 1.0 mm (Fig. 103)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310957/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 105</figureCitation>
) truncate apically, anterior apophysis broadly triangular.
</paragraph>
